# Git & PR Workflow

## Branching
- `main` — production-ready, protected. Never commit directly.
- Feature branches: `feat/short-description` (e.g. `feat/projects-section`)
- Bug fix branches: `fix/short-description` (e.g. `fix/mobile-nav-overflow`)
- Chore branches: `chore/short-description` (e.g. `chore/update-deps`)

## Commit Messages (Conventional Commits)
Format: `type(scope): short description`

Types:
- `feat` — new feature or section
- `fix` — bug fix
- `chore` — deps, config, tooling
- `style` — formatting, SCSS changes with no logic change
- `refactor` — code restructure with no behavior change
- `docs` — README, comments
- `perf` — performance improvements

Examples:
```
feat(projects): add ProjectCard component with tags
fix(hero): correct mobile layout overflow
chore(deps): update nuxt to 4.x
style(scss): extract spacing variables
```

## PRs
- Always target `main`
- Title = the commit message format above
- Description should include: what changed, why, and any testing notes
- Keep PRs focused — one feature or fix per PR
- Agent-created PRs: always create as draft unless instructed otherwise

## For Cloud Agents (Slack/Linear)
When triggered from Slack or Linear, always:
1. Create a branch from `main` using the naming convention above
2. Make changes
3. Open a draft PR to `main` with a clear description
4. Never merge — leave that for human review
